<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                    <head>No. 316.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Jackson</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-19"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 19,
                            1886</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>You are instructed to demand of the Mexican Government the instant release of
                        A. K. Cutting, a citizen of the United States, now unlawfully imprisoned at
                        Paso del Norte.</p>
                    <closer><signed>BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>